<TITLE> 3 injured as train derails </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jhenaidah, Apr 20 (bdnews24.com)  Train communication in Jessore-Poradaha section has been severed as five bogeys derailed near Darshana junction of Chuadanga. At about 2pm, 5 bogeys of Mahanada Express were derailed as it was going to Khulna from Chapainababganj. At that time three passengers were injured while getting off the bogies. They were given first aid. At 5:30 in the afternoon, SM Mahbubul Alam, the manager of west zone Pakshi division of Bangladesh Railway, told bdnews24 that a rescue train has been sent from Ishwardi towards the location of accident. The railway official said that due to the accident, the following trains were stuck on the way: Dhaka-Khulna Intercity Sundarban Express in Chuadanga, Parbotipur-Khulna Intercity Rupsha Express in Poradaha, Rajshahi-Khulna Intercity Kobadak Express in Ishwardi and Khulna-Goalanda Ghat Intercity Shagadari Express in Khulna. A passenger of the train Shapan Bagchi told bdnews24.com that as the bogies derailed two persons jumped off in panic. One woman threw her child out the window. That is how they were injured. But these persons could not be identified. bdnews24
